    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA346-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu poruḷvayiṉ pirinta talaimakaṉ āṟṟāṉāyt taṉṉeñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE who had separated for the sake of wealth said to his own heart, being unable to bear it.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA346">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kuṇakaṭaṉ mukantu kuṭakkēr piruḷit</l>
<l>            taṇkār talaiiya nilantaṇi kālai</l>
<l>            yaracupakai nuvalu marumuṉai yiyavi</l>
<l>            ṉaḻinta vēli yaṅkuṭic cīṟū</l>
<l>            rāḷiṉ maṉṟat talkuvaḷi yāṭṭat</l>
<l>            tāḷvali yākiya vaṉka ṇirukkai</l>
<l>            yiṉṟunak kaṉaimaṉ pōlā veṉṟu</l>
<l>            niṟaiyuṟu matiyi ṉilaṅkum poṟaiyaṉ</l>
<l>            peruntaṇ kollic ciṟupacuṅ kuḷavik</l>
<l>            kaṭipataṅ kamaḻuṅ kūntaṉ</l>
<l>            maṭamā varivai taṭameṉ ṟōḷē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">            At a time of coolness in the grounds that had been offered cool rain,</l>
<l rend="indent">            [clouds] drawing [water] from the eastern sea,</l>
<l rend="indent">            rising to the west [and] darkening,</l>
<l rend="indent2">            while the abiding wind drives over the village common devoid of men,</l>
<l rend="indent3">            in the small village with pretty homes [and] ruined fences</l>
<l rend="indent4">            on the way on the difficult front that tells of the king’s enmity,</l>
<l>        staying by strength that is the strength of feet,</l>
<l>        – today it does not seem as if you smiled</l>
<l rend="indent">            at the broad soft shoulders of the youthful dark woman</l>
<l rend="indent2">            with tresses that are fragrant from the height of scent</l>
<l rend="indent3">            of the little green wild jasmine from big cool Kolli hill</l>
<l rend="indent4">            of Poṟaiyaṉ who shines as the full moon, daily.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
